For running metax please run:
	1. $ npm install
	2. npm start host_metax=[metax_host:metax_port] key=[ssl_private_key_path] cert=[ssl_certificate_path] sitemap_uuid=[valid_uuid_of_sitemap] write_server_port=[http2_server_port_with_write_permissions] readonly_server_port=[http2_server_port_readonly]
	example:
		$ npm start host_metax=herbals.am:8001 key=./keys/privkey.pem cert=./keys/fullchain.pem sitemap_uuid=7756c569-a625-40d9-ae20-4a6c27d04024 read_server_port=7000 write_server_port=7001

For running test please run:
	$ npm start
	$ npm run test

NOTE: currently, logger logs only in console, for logging also in a file, please modify src/webserver.mjs' logger_options to:
{
	file_channel: {
		usage: true,
		rotation: 10,
		path: "PATH_TO_LOG_FILE"
	},
	console_channel: { usage: true },
	pattern: "%p %Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S.%i %s: %t"
}


